ned with qualitative approaches based on manual annotations in order to identify changes in text patterns on various levels by examining characteristic linguistic units.  aTextmuster lassen sich auf mehreren, miteinander verschränkten Dimensionen beschreiben. Der Band zeigt am Beispiel von empirischen Studien zur historischen Textsorten, wie sich quantitativ orientierte korpuslingustische Methoden sinnvoll mit qualitativen, auf manuellen Annotationen basierenden Zugängen verbinden lassen, um Textmusterwandel auf unterschiedlichen Ebenen und anhand charakteristischer sprachlicher Einheiten zu erkennen.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aHistorische Textlinguistik. 4aKorpuslinguistische Methoden. 4aNeuhochdeutsch. 4aSprachgeschichte. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Historical & Comparative.2bisacsh  aCorpus Linguistics.  aHistorical Text Linguistics.  aHistory of Language.1 aDammel, Antje, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeorgi, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaaf, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaaf, Susanne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHabermann, Mechthild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHausendorf, Heiko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHennig, Mathilde, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKempf, Luise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrokowski, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLasch, Alexander, econtributor